---
/**
 * lsm-compaction-deep-dive · Figure 2 — Level 1 "THE IRON LAW": the three
 * amplification cards (write = disk÷app bytes, read = SSTables touched per read,
 * space = disk÷live bytes) and who pays for each.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/storage-engines/lsm-compaction-deep-dive.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). It lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the
 * MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses
 * kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size, stroke-width, …). This figure
 * references no arrowhead markers, so it needs no local <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 560 200"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Three amplification factors: write amplification is disk bytes over app bytes, read amplification is SSTables touched per read, space amplification is disk bytes over live bytes"
    >
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <rect
                x="10"
                y="40"
                width="170"
                height="120"
                rx="10"
                fill="#f7ecea"
                stroke="#9a2417"
                stroke-width="1.4"></rect>
            <text x="95" y="62" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
                >WRITE amp</text
            >
            <text x="95" y="92" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" fill="#111110"
                >disk bytes</text
            >
            <line x1="48" y1="100" x2="142" y2="100" stroke="#6b675f"></line>
            <text x="95" y="116" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" fill="#111110"
                >app bytes</text
            >
            <text x="95" y="144" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >pays: flash wear,<tspan x="95" dy="11">write throughput</tspan></text
            >
            <rect
                x="195"
                y="40"
                width="170"
                height="120"
                rx="10"
                fill="#eef2f5"
                stroke="#1f3a5a"
                stroke-width="1.4"></rect>
            <text
                x="280"
                y="62"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">READ amp</text
            >
            <text x="280" y="92" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" fill="#111110"
                >SSTables (disk reads)</text
            >
            <text x="280" y="108" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" fill="#111110"
                >touched per read</text
            >
            <text x="280" y="144" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >pays: read latency,<tspan x="280" dy="11">p99</tspan></text
            >
            <rect
                x="380"
                y="40"
                width="170"
                height="120"
                rx="10"
                fill="#eef5ee"
                stroke="#2f5d3a"
                stroke-width="1.4"></rect>
            <text
                x="465"
                y="62"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">SPACE amp</text
            >
            <text x="465" y="92" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" fill="#111110"
                >bytes on disk</text
            >
            <line x1="418" y1="100" x2="512" y2="100" stroke="#6b675f"></line>
            <text x="465" y="116" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" fill="#111110"
                >live data bytes</text
            >
            <text x="465" y="144" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >pays: storage cost</text
            >
            <text
                x="280"
                y="24"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">THE IRON LAW — lower one, raise another</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Every compaction strategy is just a point that trades these three off against each other.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
